Preamble: My Government Decision dated 27th September, 2024 at Reference No. (1) declares the cash prizes and the procedure for appropriation of these prize money to the winning local bodies in the 12 groups of GERT Mission 4.0. Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meetings held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.

Government Decision: Considering the points mentioned in the Preamble, the total amount received by the Modale Gram Panchayat under Maji Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 is Rs. The works to be taken up out of the prize money of Rs. The Detailed Project Report (DPR) worth ₹1 crore (₹1.23 lakh) was submitted by the Village Development Officer, Modale Gram Panchayat with the technical approval of the Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad, Nashik.

The works in the Detailed Project Report costing 1,56,232, 378.00 (Rupees One Crore Rupees Sixty Two Thousand Three Hundred and Seventy Eight Only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions:
The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
2. Terms and Conditions
1) The functioning mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report will remain a broken Gram Panchayat.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) If the amount of the prize exceeds the amount, it should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. The Gram Panchayat broken under Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan was ranked first at the state level in the "Gram Panchayat Group (population less than 1.5-2,500)" category with Rs.1.00 crores and highest land in Ale region.

For performance, Rs. A total of Rs. A prize money of ₹1.50 crore has been received. Out of the prize money of Rs. The first instalment of ₹1 lakh has been disbursed to them. The detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money was accorded administrative approval by the Government as per paragraph 1 above.

Hence, the remaining prize money of Rs. 75.00 Lakh (Rs. Seventy-five lakh only) is being approved by the government for disbursement of the second instalment through the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
